				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Kitchen Rush (Revised Edition): Time for Dessert!" />
			
						                               				
				<name type="alternate" sortindex="1" value="Kitchen Rush (Revised Edition): Aber bitte mit Sahne" />
			
						               													<description>It wasn't long ago that the players bought an old restaurant and received their first guests. Their restaurant grew, more demanding guests came and they were able to hire more staff. Unfortunately, the success didn't last long and the restaurant became quiet. The number of guests decreased, temporary workers had to be let go and not all damage in the restaurant could be repaired. So the players decided that the restaurant needed a change. It is high time to add a pastry shop to the restaurant and serve sweet desserts: tiramisu, cr&amp;egrave;me br&amp;ucirc;l&amp;eacute;e and fancy sundaes &amp;ndash; because it's Time for Dessert!?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The expansion Time for Dessert! introduces a new type of order. By taking advantage of additional actions and using ingredients such as fruit, cream and ice cream, the players have to satisfy the demanding wishes of the guests. A specialist helps to carry out actions twice in one go, but also needs more time to do so. If the players use their earned money for investments, these bring advantages in every shift. As in the basic game, all new rules are conveyed over the course of several scenarios.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;While the story begins after the end of the last Kitchen Rush scenario, players only need to know the rules of the first four scenarios in order to play the expansion. Each of the seven new scenarios introduces new elements. Each group can decide for themselves whether they play the entire campaign or simply repeat the scenario that they enjoy the most.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
